I was able to work around this problem by implementing an `ExceptionMapper` to catch the `ProcessingException`. First, I tried to implement an `ExceptionMapper` for `JsonbException` but later realized that `JsonbException` was further wrapped by `ProcessingException`. Using `ExceptionMapper` for `ProcessingException` to catch the exception and then mapping to `BadRequest` Response solved the issue. 


    @Provider
    public class ProcessingExceptionMapper implements ExceptionMapper&lt;ProcessingException&gt; {
        @Override
        public Response toResponse(ProcessingException exception) {
           String defaultMessage = &quot;Unable to process request body&quot;;
            return Response.status(Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST)
                           .entity(defaultMessage)
                           .type(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
                           .build();
        }
    }

